<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,441,1007]" pageId="1" pageNumber="281">
A male specimen was designated as the 
<typeStatus box="[641,739,585,611]" pageId="1" pageNumber="281">holotype</typeStatus>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Murayama, S." box="[779,983,585,611]" pageId="1" pageNumber="281" pagination="170 - 175" refId="ref5950" refString="Murayama, S. (1943) Uber einige Lycaeniden und Hesperiiden von Formosa. Zephyrus, 9 (3), 170 - 175. [in Japanese]" type="journal article" year="1943">Murayama (1943)</bibRefCitation>
, and the specimen was retrieved in 
<collectionCode box="[1376,1437,585,611]" country="Japan" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/pcbg-hhf5" name="Lake Biwa Museum" pageId="1" pageNumber="281">LBM</collectionCode>
(
<figureCitation box="[159,267,621,647]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–18" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1896,1921]" captionTargetBox="[172,1429,181,1871]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[159,1429,181,1871]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 1–18. 1–3. Ampittia matudai Murayama, 1943, holotype; 4–6. Erynnis montanus neomontanus Murayama &amp; Yoshisaka, 1959, holotype; 7–9. Ochlodes siva yuchingkina Murayama &amp; Shimonoya, 1962, holotype; 10–12. Aeromachus bandaishanus Murayama &amp; Shimonoya, 1968, holotype; 13–15. Pseudocoladenia pinsbukana Shimonoya &amp; Murayama, 1976, holotype; 16–18. Polytremis zina taiwana Murayama, 1981, holotype. Scale bar = 1 cm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3990959" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3990959/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="281">Figs. 1–3</figureCitation>
; Dried Insect Database Reg. no. 1500022019).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,441,1007]" pageId="1" pageNumber="281">
Additional specimens of the species were not reported until 
<bibRefCitation author="Murayama, S." box="[865,1067,656,683]" pageId="1" pageNumber="281" pagination="1 - 4" refId="ref5980" refString="Murayama, S. (1955) New or little known Rhopalocera from China and Korea. Tyo to Ga, 6 (1), 1 - 4." type="journal article" year="1955">Murayama (1955)</bibRefCitation>
found a pair in Sugitani’s collection deposited at Kyushu University. HC tried to locate those specimens, but they were removed from the collection and no record was kept as to who loaned or took them. Subsequent records of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Murayama" authorityYear="1943" box="[1033,1125,729,755]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Ampittia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="281" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="matudai">
<emphasis box="[1033,1125,729,755]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="281">matudai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Lin, C. C." box="[1140,1247,729,755]" pageId="1" pageNumber="281" refId="ref5891" refString="Lin, C. C. (1994) The Butterflies and Nature of Taiwan. Three Pigs Internatinonal Ltd, Taipei, 162 pp." type="book" year="1994">Lin 1994</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Lin, C. C. &amp; Su, J. P." box="[1258,1429,729,755]" pageId="1" pageNumber="281" refId="ref5917" refString="Lin, C. C. &amp; Su, J. P. (2013) The Photographic Book of all Butterflies in Taiwan. Green World, Yilan, 420 pp." type="book" year="2013">Lin &amp; Su 2013</bibRefCitation>
) turned out to be either 
<taxonomicName authority="(Menetries, 1858) (Hsu et al. 2019)" baseAuthorityName="Menetries" baseAuthorityYear="1858" box="[401,919,764,791]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Ampittia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="281" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="inachus">
<emphasis box="[401,519,765,791]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="281">A. inachus</emphasis>
(Ménétriés, 1858) (
<bibRefCitation author="Hsu Y. F. &amp; Chiba, H. &amp; Tsukiyama, H. &amp; Liang, J. Y. &amp; Huang, C. W." box="[739,911,765,791]" pageId="1" pageNumber="281" refId="ref5271" refString="Hsu Y. F., Chiba, H., Tsukiyama, H., Liang, J. Y. &amp; Huang, C. W. (2019) Butterfly Fauna of Taiwan. Vol. III. Hesperiidae. Forest Bureau, C. O. A., Taipei, 364 pp." type="book" year="2019">
Hsu 
<emphasis box="[792,847,765,791]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="281">et al.</emphasis>
2019
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
or 
<taxonomicName authority="Murayama &amp; Shimonoya, 1968" authorityName="Murayama &amp; Shimonoya" authorityYear="1968" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Aeromachus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="281" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bandaishanus">
<emphasis box="[954,1140,765,791]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="281">A. bandaishanus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Murayama, S. &amp; Shimonoya, T." pageId="1" pageNumber="281" pagination="1 - 16" refId="ref6271" refString="Murayama, S. &amp; Shimonoya, T. (1968) A contribution to taxonomy of the Formosan butterflies, with descriptions of 1 new species, 1 new race, 1 unrecorded species, and 11 new aberrant forms. New Entomologist, 17 (1), 1 - 16. [in Japanese]" type="journal article" year="1968">Murayama &amp; Shimonoya, 1968</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Hsu, Y. F." box="[223,337,801,827]" pageId="1" pageNumber="281" refId="ref5232" refString="Hsu, Y. F. (2013) The Butterflies of Taiwan. Vol. 1. Hesperiidae, Papilionidae and Pieridae. Morning Star Publishing Inc., Taichung, 397 pp. [in Chinese]" type="book" year="2013">Hsu 2013</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Sugisaka, Y." box="[349,520,801,827]" pageId="1" pageNumber="281" pagination="19 - 24" refId="ref6472" refString="Sugisaka, Y. (2018) On the significant differences of macula mutation in Taiwan species type Aeromachus bandaishanus and A. matudai. Yadoriga, 259, 19 - 24. [in Japanese]" type="journal article" year="2018">Sugisaka 2018</bibRefCitation>
). YFH undertook investigations at the 
<typeStatus box="[959,1007,801,827]" pageId="1" pageNumber="281">type</typeStatus>
locality of the taxon every year since 1982 searching for the species but in vain. The vicinity of the area was covered with decent vegetation before the end of World War II but was later severely deforested and disturbed due to horticultural practice.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,441,1007]" pageId="1" pageNumber="281">
We regard 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Murayama" authorityYear="1943" box="[319,411,909,935]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Ampittia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="281" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="matudai">
<emphasis box="[319,411,909,935]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="281">matudai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a valid specific name in the genus 
<taxonomicName authority="de Niceville, 1890" authorityName="de Niceville" authorityYear="1890" box="[822,1170,909,935]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Aeromachus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="281" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[822,961,909,935]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="281">Aeromachus</emphasis>
de Nicéville, 1890
</taxonomicName>
following the treatment in 
<bibRefCitation author="Chiba, H. &amp; Hsu, Y. F. &amp; Shirozu, T." box="[180,392,945,971]" pageId="1" pageNumber="281" pagination="130 - 132" refId="ref4961" refString="Chiba, H., Hsu, Y. F. &amp; Shirozu, T. (1992) Hesperiidae. In: Heppner, J. N. &amp; Inoue, H. (Eds.), Lepidoptera of Taiwan. Vol. 1. Part 2. Checklist. Association for Tropical Lepidoptera, Gainesville, pp. 130 - 132." type="book chapter" year="1992">
<collectingRegion box="[180,247,945,971]" country="Japan" name="Chiba" pageId="1" pageNumber="281">Chiba</collectingRegion>
<emphasis box="[254,310,945,971]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="281">et al.</emphasis>
(1992)
</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Hsu Y. F. &amp; Chiba, H. &amp; Tsukiyama, H. &amp; Liang, J. Y. &amp; Huang, C. W." box="[446,640,945,971]" pageId="1" pageNumber="281" refId="ref5271" refString="Hsu Y. F., Chiba, H., Tsukiyama, H., Liang, J. Y. &amp; Huang, C. W. (2019) Butterfly Fauna of Taiwan. Vol. III. Hesperiidae. Forest Bureau, C. O. A., Taipei, 364 pp." type="book" year="2019">
Hsu 
<emphasis box="[499,555,945,971]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="281">et al.</emphasis>
(2019)
</bibRefCitation>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Huang, H." box="[651,807,945,971]" pageId="1" pageNumber="281" refId="ref5439" refString="Huang, H. (2009) Systematic and Taxonomic Study on the tribe Aeromachini Tutt (Lepidoptera: Hesperiidae) from China. Master thesis. Shanghai Normal University, Shanghai, 175 pp." type="book" year="2009">Huang (2009)</bibRefCitation>
considered that the taxon should be treated as a subspecies of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Evans, 1939)" baseAuthorityName="Evans" baseAuthorityYear="1939" box="[232,483,981,1007]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Aeromachus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="281" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jesta">
<emphasis box="[232,316,981,1007]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="281">A. jesta</emphasis>
(Evans, 1939)
</taxonomicName>
. This point of view awaits further evaluation.
</paragraph>
